<introduction>
<p>
This a tutorial on the computer algebra system Macaulay2 via the package <url href="https://macaulay2.com/doc/Macaulay2/share/doc/Macaulay2/InvariantRing/html/index.html"><c>InvariantRing</c></url> by <url href="https://msp.org/jsag/2013/5-1/p03.xhtml"> Hawes (2013) </url> and <url href="10.2140/jsag.2024.14.5">Ferraro et.al. (2020)</url>. The package is designed to compute invariants of linearly reductive actions, based partially on the book <url href="https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007%252F978-3-662-48422-7"><em>Computational Invariant Theory</em> (2015)</url> by H. Derksen and G. Kemper. 
</p>
